revision.text:
The '''American Specialty Toy Retailing Association''', or ''ASTRA'', is an [[organization]] of [[manufacturers]], manufacturers representatives, [[distributor]]s and [[retail]]ers of [[specialty toys]] (as compared to [[mass market]] product).
The American Specialty Toy Retailing Association (ASTRA) is a non-profit association that provides leadership and resources to grow the specialty toy industry. It is the largest association serving the specialty toy industry. ASTRA members build their businesses around specialty toys, which generally are designed with a focus on what the [[child]] can do, rather than what the toy can do.
==Neighborhood Toy Store Day== In 2010, ASTRA established Neighborhood [[Toy stores|Toy Store]] Day, to be observed on the second Saturday of each November.<ref>Yahoo Finance: [https://finance.yahoo.com/news/shop-local-support-community-neighborhood-143000077.htm Shop Local, Support The Community This "Neighborhood Toy Store Day]</ref><ref>The Oklahoman [http://newsok.com/oklahoma-city-area-stores-plan-events-for-neighborhood-toy-store-day-on-nov.-9/article/3899269 Oklahoma City-area stores plan events for Neighborhood Toy Store Day]</ref><ref>Metro Parent: [http://www.metroparent.com/Metro-Parent/November-2011/Neighborhood-Toy-Store-Day-in-Southeast-Michigan Neighborhood Toy Store Day]</ref>
