'''Arthur Joseph Rooney II''' (born September 14, 1952) is the owner of the [[Pittsburgh Steelers]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.steelers.com/team/front-office.html |title=Front Office Staff &#124; Pittsburgh Steelers |publisher=Steelers.com |date= |accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref>

==Early life==
Rooney graduated from the [[University of Pittsburgh]] in 1978 with a [[B.A.]] in [[Political Science]].<ref name="steelers1">{{cite web|url=http://www.steelers.com/history/tradition-of-excellence.html |title=Pittsburgh Steelers &#124; Tradition of Excellence |publisher=Steelers.com |date= |accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref> He then attended [[Duquesne University]]’s School of Law, where he earned his [[Juris Doctor|J.D.]] degree in 1982.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://law.pitt.edu/art-rooney-ii-deliver-pitt-school-law-commencement-address-may-11 |title=Art Rooney II to Deliver Pitt School of Law Commencement Address May 11 &#124; PittLaw |publisher=Law.pitt.edu |date=2014-09-24 |accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref><ref name="steelers1"/>

==Career==
The eldest of nine children of longtime Steelers chairman [[Dan Rooney]],<ref name=stake>{{cite web|last=Bouchette |first=Ed |url=http://www.post-gazette.com/sports/steelers/2016/02/28/Some-Rooneys-ready-to-give-up-shares-in-Steelers/stories/201602280078 |title=Breaking the huddle, some Rooneys ready to give up shares in Steelers &#124; Pittsburgh Post-Gazette |publisher=Post-gazette.com |date=2016-02-28 |accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref> he is the grandson of Steelers' founder “The Chief”, [[Art Rooney, Sr.]] He was named team president in May 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://old.post-gazette.com/steelers/20030722rooney0722p1.asp |title=Art Rooney II replaces father as Steelers president |publisher=Old.post-gazette.com |date=2003-07-22 |accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref> Prior to that, he served as vice president and general counsel of the Steelers, and has served on the board of directors of the Steelers since 1989. He currently serves as chairman of the NFL’s Stadium Committee, and serves on numerous NFL boards, including the Legislative Committee, the Management Council Executive Committee, the International Committee and the Digital Media Committee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/blog/afcnorth/post/_/id/84012/pittsburgh-steelers-ownership-at-a-glance |title=Pittsburgh Steelers ownership at a glance - AFC North |publisher=ESPN |date=2015-03-18 |accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref> Prior to his father's 2017 death, Rooney II held a 30% stake in the Steelers franchise<ref name=stake/> and was in line to inherit most of the 30% share Dan Rooney held, which would make Rooney II the majority owner of the team. He is one of only two third-generation owners in the league, the other being [[John Mara]], to whom he is related by marriage (Mara's brother is married to Rooney's sister, and both owners count actresses [[Rooney Mara]] and [[Kate Mara]] as nieces.)

He currently holds an [[Of Counsel]] position with the law firm Buchanan Ingersoll & Rooney. He is active in the [[Pittsburgh]] community, devoting a substantial amount of his time to various organizations. He currently serves on the boards of the [[Pittsburgh Public Theater]],<ref>{{cite web|author=Teresa Varley Steelers.com @Teresa_Varley |url=http://www.steelers.com/news/article-1/Rooney-honored-by-Pittsburgh-Public-Theater/fdc59963-4216-4423-a272-55aeecd53b22 |title=Rooney honored by Pittsburgh Public Theater |publisher=Steelers.com |date=2012-05-20 |accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref> [[Saint Vincent College]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Cohen |first=Max |url=http://www.post-gazette.com/sports/2015/07/24/Steelers-celebrating-50-years-at-Saint-Vincent-College/stories/201507240110 |title=Steelers faithful: 50 years at Saint Vincent &#124; Pittsburgh Post-Gazette |publisher=Post-gazette.com |date=2015-07-24 |accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref> Senator John Heinz Western PA History center<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heinzhistorycenter.org/about/administration/board-of-trustees |title=Board of Trustees |publisher=Heinz History Center |date=2014-06-20 |accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref> and the [[United Way of America]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Teresa Varley Steelers.com @Teresa_Varley |url=http://www.steelers.com/news/article-1/Steelers-continue-to-team-up-with-United-Way/582e9838-55a6-4133-90ff-a814003ca004 |title=Steelers continue to team up with United Way |publisher=Steelers.com |date=2015-11-16 |accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref> 

==Personal life==
Rooney is married to Greta, and they have four children.<ref name="steelers1"/>

